y measuring dimensions, such as length, height, and distance between reference points.  Performs needed tests on site and in the laboratory to ensure Conformity of material and works according to the contract specifications.  Performs Calculation of BBS for steel cutting, bending, binding, weight calculation as well as Reconciliation.  Maintained and Provides Quantity of required materials on site and on Store on time.  Proper execution of work such as (Leveling, excavation, footing, columns, beams, slabs, Brick works, plasters, plumbing, electrical conduit & wiring, flooring, painting, Finishing etc.) as per drawing.  Checking the all block works, internal and external plastering & fall ceiling works.  Marking, Checking & site execution for all finishing works.  Labors, masons, carpenters, steel fitters, plumbers,& electrician’s arrangements as per the site requirement.  Constant coordination with every aspect to make the project commence without delay.  Planning in advance to the daily activities to maximize the available resources.  Proper monitoring the daily accomplishment of the project and Prepare progress report for evaluation. || CIVIL ENGINEER | MCS PROJECTS PVT. LTD NOIDA, U.P | 2020-2022 | Key Deliverables  Monitoring Kent RO plant (commercial construction) from the start ie., from boundary wall.  Ensuring all constructional activities like Layout, Leveling, Excavation, Casting, Brickwork, steel BBS, BOQ, M Roll, DPR, etc.  Performing Laboratory and Onsite tests for checking the materials and their strengths like, sand, aggregates, Bricks, Cement, Steels RMC etc.  Directing and overseeing the activities of sub contractors.  Setting contractor schedules and delivery dates for ongoing projects.  Ensuring materials availabilities, delays (due to conflicting project elements).  Consulting with clients(accompanying the client during site visit, answering questions about construction projects and overall progress)  Overseeing the Project Budget by seeking the opportunities to save by reducing wasteful practices and increasing efficiency.  Maintaining Site Safety by ensuring that contractors and crews are following proper safety protocols like wearing helmets, safety shoes, safety jackets belts and working is accomplishing as per Indian Standards.  Preparing site reports on regular Basis. || CIVIL ENGINEER | PC GUPTA & COMPANY PVT. LTD. GURUGRAM | 2022-2023 | Key Deliverables Road Construction  Supervised construction for Flexible Pavements for layers of earth work(Fly ash & soil),Sub grade, Drainage layer, GSB,WMM,DBM,BC as per MOST and contract specifications for different typical cross-sections.  Field inspections for laying layers, density, compaction and quality maintenance for different typical cross-sections.  To Control the work execution in quality at site as per MOST Specifications (i.e. Road alignment thickness, camber, designed levels).  Fixing of alignment of roads and minor structures through Total Station.  Check the top level of each pavement layers for the entire stretch.  Preparation weekly and monthly reports jointly with RE & ARE’S for progress of work.  Maintain the daily reports and daily diaries for future reference. Drain construction Work  Marking for earth excavation as per approved drawing by GMDA.  Taking the material quantities for all civil related jobs.  Raising the site material requisition order & co-ordinate with suppliers to get the materials at correct time.  Inspecting & Checking, the all civil related works after completion of works from my side.  Performs Calculation of BBS of Drain for steel cutting, bending, binding, weight calculation as well as Reconciliation.  Performs needed tests on site and in the laboratory to ensure Conformity of material and works according to the contract specifications.  Handling Self Concrete Loading Machine as per approved design mix ratio. PIONEER E SOLUTIONS PVT. LTD. (CONSULTANCY) || ASSISTANT ENGINEER (AE) | Telecommunications India Limited(TCIL) | 2023-Present | Location: Jammu & Kashmir Project : Navodaya Vidyalaya , Kishtwar, Palmar J&K."}]'::jsonb, '[{"title":"Imported project details","description":"J S University Sikohabad 62% || 2019 B.TECH (Civil | https://B.TECH | 2019-2019 || Engineering) || Rawal Institute of Engineering and || Technology, Affiliated by Maharishi || Dayanand University, Rohtak || 76.4% | https://76.4% || 2014 12th (CBSE) M.V. Convent Inter College, Allahabad 58% | https://M.V. | 2014-2014"}]'::jsonb, '[{"title":"Imported accomplishment","description":" Participated in International mathematics Olympiad, on 10th Dec, 2009.;  Secured 2nd position, in national volleyball tournament, 2009.;  A and B certification by NCC, 2012-13."}]'::jsonb, 'F:\Resume All 1\Resume PDF\DEEPAK MISHRA.pdf', 'Name: Deepak Mishra

